00:16:48.940 --> 00:16:51.440
Well, if you don't like that idea...

330
00:16:53.940 --> 00:16:57.440
We have other ways of rendering you immobile.

331
00:16:59.140 --> 00:17:01.140
You'll be fine.

332
00:17:01.140 --> 00:17:03.340
As soon as we finish our business,

333
00:17:03.340 --> 00:17:06.540
we'll leave you all alone.

334
00:17:06.540 --> 00:17:08.840
If you're lucky and the real man of this household

335
00:17:08.840 --> 00:17:12.640
comes back from his business trip early,

336
00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:14.640
he may be able to help you.

337
00:17:16.240 --> 00:17:17.940
My, what could it be?

338
00:17:17.940 --> 00:17:19.740
That "business" of yours.

339
00:17:19.740 --> 00:17:23.040
Well, there's no telling, is there?

340
00:17:28.740 --> 00:17:30.740
Hey, hurry and answer it.

341
00:17:30.740 --> 00:17:31.740
Yes, sure.

342
00:17:31.740 --> 00:17:33.740
Hey, could that be...

343
00:17:33.740 --> 00:17:35.940
Conan, right?

344
00:17:35.940 --> 00:17:36.940
Hello.

345
00:17:36.940 --> 00:17:38.740
I'm from the post office.

346
00:17:38.740 --> 00:17:42.340
Is this Mr. Uemura from Room 2806?

347
00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:44.040
Yes, it is.

348
00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:46.440
Regarding a registered mail you sent for delivery,

349
00:17:46.440 --> 00:17:48.240
the addressee was unavailable,

350
00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:50.540
so we were unable to deliver it.

351
00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:53.340
Yes, it seems they've moved.

352
00:17:53.340 --> 00:17:54.940
In that case, since this is registered mail,

353
00:17:54.940 --> 00:17:58.440
